commit.message:
Remove leftover noise from VERSION/SOVERSION variables

Commit 56088f9bf6c2 removed the CACHE keyword from the
set command, which made the trailing help text part of the
variable values. This extra text was propagated to the
pkgconfig file, making it malformed.

As there is no use for any help text (e.g. in CMake GUI) for a
variable which can not be overridden by a user, remove the
trailing text.

Fixes #55

On win32 dll were only properly exported for the double precision
variant because the automatically added cminpack_EXPORTS was the only
one take into account from cminpack.h
now we use CMINPACK_DLL_EXPORTS for all variants to fix the build
